1980 VINTAGE

Wise wine-lovers have long been aware that so-called “off” vintages provide excellent opportunities in high quality wines at low prices. Robert Parker in Connoisseur magazine comments: “The /980, sandwiched between a succession of top years in Bordeaux, has become a forgotten stepchild. However, the shrewd and adventurous wine enthusiast knows how surprisingly good the best wines from this vintage are.... The 1980 clarets are fully mature, with few exceptions, and offer delicious drinking now.”

In summary, if you want to enjoy top-flight Bordeaux at modest cost, do not overlook the 1980 vintage.
